COMMERCIAL LICENSING

The terms set forth above apply to non-commercial use, open-source projects,
academic research, and evaluation purposes. For enterprises, organizations,
government agencies, and commercial entities requiring additional rights,
protections, services, or flexibility, StrataLogic Solutions Inc. offers a
range of commercial licensing options designed to meet the specific needs
of businesses of all sizes.

COMMERCIAL LICENSE FEATURES AND BENEFITS

Enterprise Support: Priority technical support with guaranteed response
times, dedicated account management, and direct access to engineering
teams for critical issue resolution. Support includes telephone support,
email support, ticketing system access, and a dedicated support portal.

Legal Indemnification: Comprehensive indemnification against intellectual
property infringement claims, copyright claims, patent claims, trade secret
claims, and other third-party legal actions arising from the use of the
software. Indemnification includes defense costs, settlement coverage, and
judgment coverage up to agreed limits.

Liability Protection: Negotiated limitations on liability that provide
protection against catastrophic financial exposure, with liability caps
tailored to the specific needs, risk profile, and business context of the
enterprise customer.

White-Label Distribution: Complete rights to remove StrataLogic Solutions Inc.
branding, acknowledgment requirements, attribution obligations, and any
other identifying marks from the software, allowing for seamless integration
into your own branded products, services, and offerings without any external
attribution or reference to StrataLogic Solutions Inc.

Custom Development: Priority access to StrataLogic Solutions Inc. engineering
resources for the development of custom features, integrations, optimizations,
extensions, plugins, modules, and modifications specifically tailored to
your business requirements, with guaranteed delivery timelines and dedicated
project management.

Extended Warranty: Commercial warranties that go beyond the standard "AS IS"
disclaimer, including performance guarantees, availability commitments,
defect correction obligations, security assurance, and compliance guarantees,
with service level agreements and financial remedies for non-performance.

Source Code Escrow: Deposit of complete and up-to-date source code with a
neutral third-party escrow agent, ensuring continued access and maintenance
capabilities in the event of bankruptcy, acquisition, discontinuation of
product, or any other unforeseen circumstances affecting StrataLogic
Solutions Inc.

Audit Rights: Full rights to audit the software for security compliance,
performance benchmarking, vulnerability assessment, code quality analysis,
regulatory adherence, and any other technical or compliance-related reviews,
with access to internal testing reports and security assessments.

Patent Protection: Express patent grants covering the use of any StrataLogic
Solutions Inc. patents, patent applications, or patent rights that may be
implicated by the software, providing additional protection against patent
litigation and freedom to operate.

Flexible Licensing Models: Licensing options including per-developer,
per-seat, per-application, per-server, per-CPU core, per-user, per-site,
enterprise-wide, and unlimited global licenses, with volume discounts and
custom pricing available for large-scale deployments.

Long-Term Support: Extended maintenance and security update commitments
with guaranteed support periods of up to ten years for enterprise customers,
including backported security fixes and critical patches.

Training and Certification: Comprehensive training programs for development
and operations teams, including on-site workshops, virtual training sessions,
webinars, documentation access, and certification programs.

Integration Assistance: Dedicated assistance with integrating the software
into existing infrastructure, including compatibility testing, migration
planning, deployment optimization, performance tuning, and troubleshooting.

Regulatory Compliance: Support for compliance with industry regulations
including GDPR, CCPA, HIPAA, SOC 2, ISO 27001, PCI DSS, FedRAMP, NIST,
and other applicable standards, with necessary documentation and
certifications.

Audit Defense: Assistance with responding to third-party audits, including
audit support, documentation preparation, and expert testimony if required.

SLA Guarantees: Service Level Agreements with guaranteed uptime, performance
metrics, response times, and financial credits for failures to meet
commitments.

Multi-Version Support: Support for multiple versions of the software
simultaneously, allowing organizations to maintain legacy deployments
while transitioning to newer versions.

Regular Updates: Scheduled updates, feature releases, performance
improvements, and security patches delivered on a predictable and
coordinated schedule.

Customization: Tailored modifications to the software to meet specific
business requirements, including custom features, integrations, reporting
capabilities, and user interface enhancements.

